    • Constructor Detail

      • LogEntry

        public LogEntry​(int id,
                int admintype,
                String admindata,
                int caid,
                int module,
                Date time,
                String username,
                String certificatesnr,
                int event,
                String comment)
        Function used by EJBCA to log information.
        Parameters:
        id - ID
        admintype - is pricipally the type of data stored in the admindata field, should be one of org.ejbca.core.model.log.Admin.TYPE_ constants.
        admindata - is the data identifying the administrator, should be certificate snr or ip-address when no certificate could be retrieved.
        caid - CA ID
        module - indicates from which module the event was logged. i.e one of the constans LogConstants.MODULE_RA, LogConstants.MODULE_CA ....
        time - the time the event occured.
        username - the name of the user involved or null if no user is involved.
        certificatesnr - the certificate involved in the event or null if no certificate is involved.
        event - id of the event, should be one of the org.ejbca.core.model.log.LogConstants.EVENT_ constants.
        comment - comment of the event.
